==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prunello
<hw>Pru*nel"lo</hw>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. <ets>prunelle</ets>, probably so called from its color
resembling that of prunes. See <er>Prune</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<def>A smooth woolen stuff, generally black, used for making shoes; a
kind of lasting; -- formerly used also for clergymen's gowns.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prunelle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prunello
<hw>Pru*nel"lo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>prunelle</ets>, dim. of <ets>prune</ets>. See <er>Prune</er> a
plum.]</ety> <def>A species of dried plum; prunelle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pruner</ent>⟦br⟧
